0! We’re going to pause for the holidays, and resume the first week of January.  Please weigh in on the tickets below — your voice and feedback are welcome!  Issues / Discussions: Blocks: Headings block: [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Kjell Reigstad\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4598:\"<p>Hello! This is the 32nd weekly roundup of theme-related discussions, fixes, and developments in Gutenberg. This is the last update of 2020! We’re going to pause for the holidays, and resume the first week of January. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please weigh in on the tickets below — your voice and feedback are welcome! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Issues / Discussions:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Blocks: Headings block: add support for font weight. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27639\">27639</a></li><li>Blocks: File Block: Turn the button into a button block. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27760\">27760</a></li><li>Blocks: RSS Block: Additional configurations. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27766\">27766</a></li><li>Blocks: Navigation Block: Fix the text color for links. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/26698\">26698</a></li><li>Blocks: Headings Block: Add support for font weight. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27639\">27639</a></li><li>FSE: Discussion about improvements to block-styles loading. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27671\">27671</a></li><li>FSE: Allow support for custom templates in block-based themes. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27778\">27778</a></li><li>FSE: Load content in an iFrame. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/25775\">25775</a></li><li>FSE: Strip directory from theme taxonomy. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27765\">27765</a></li><li>FSE: Consider adding block-editor class to the site editor. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27724\">27724</a></li><li>FSE Blocks: Support wide/full alignments for the Query block container. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27589\">27589</a></li><li>FSE Blocks: Allow Post Featured Image blocks to have a consistent height. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27620\">27620</a></li><li>FSE Blocks: Comments Form: Convert button into a button block. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27740\">27740</a> </li><li>Global Styles: Change the behaviour of the reset button <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27483\">27483</a></li></ul><p>Merged/fixed:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Blocks: Add custom units to box control. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27626\">27626</a></li><li>Blocks: RSS Block: Add border-box CSS. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27767\">27767</a></li><li>FSE Blocks: Add comment form block styles. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27673\">27673</a></li></ul><p>Overview Issues:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Full Site Editing Milestones. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24551\">24551</a></li><li>Template Tags in Full Site Editing. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/22724\">22724</a> </li><li>Missing query block functionality. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24934\">24934</a></li><li>Query and Loop block tracking: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24762\">24762</a></li></ul><p>General Resources:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/labels/%5BFeature%5D%20Full%20Site%20Editing\">GitHub Issues: Full Site Editing</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/labels/%5BFeature%5D%20Themes\">GitHub  Issues: Themes</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/blob/master/docs/designers-developers/developers/themes/block-based-themes.md\">Block-based Themes Reference</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/tutorials/block-based-themes/\">Block-based Themes Tutorial</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/developers/themes/theme-json/\">Experimental-Themes.json</a></li><li><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/07/05/using-the-block-editor-for-theme-parts/\">Using the Block Editor for Theme Parts</a></li><li><a href=\"https://wp.me/p29gdg-4MC\">Printing navigation-block HTML from a legacy menu in themes</a></li></ul><p>Thanks to <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/joen/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>joen</a> and <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/scruffian/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>scruffian</a> for help pulling this post together. Please let us know if it was helpful in the comments!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/tags/gutenberg-themes-roundup/\" class=\"tag\"><span class=\"tag-prefix\">#</span>gutenberg-themes-roundup</a></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/12/18/gutenberg-themes-week-of-dec-14-2020/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:30:\"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1\";a:1:{s:7:\"post-id\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"19830\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"Block Themes Meeting Notes for 16 December 2020\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/12/16/block-themes-meeting-notes-for-16-december-2020/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/12/16/block-themes-meeting-notes-for-16-december-2020/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 16 Dec 2020 16:30:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Uncategorized\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"themereview\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/?p=19823\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:320:\"Channel: #themereview Facilitated by @kjellr Gutenberg + Themes Highlights WordPress 5.6 was released last week. Header blocks will soon have a font-weight setting We want to load the Site Editor in an iFrame to give us a clean slate for styles in the front and back end. Custom units are now an option for the [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"scruffian\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2862:\"<p>Channel: <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/tags/themereview/\" class=\"tag\"><span class=\"tag-prefix\">#</span>themereview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Facilitated by <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kjellr/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>kjellr</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Gutenberg + Themes Highlights</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>WordPress 5.6 was <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/news/2020/12/simone/\">released last week</a>.</li><li>Header blocks will soon <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27639\">have a font-weight setting</a></li><li>We want to <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/25775\">load the Site Editor in an iFrame</a> to give us a clean slate for styles in the front and back end.</li><li>Custom units are <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27626\">now an option for the spacing control</a>.</li></ul><p>There are more Gutenberg updates in <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/12/11/gutenberg-themes-week-of-dec-7-2020/\">the latest Gutenberg + Themes post</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Twenty Twenty-One (TT1) Blocks</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Work is accelerating on the new Block version of TwentyTwentyOne. This is centered around <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/theme-experiments/projects/1\">this project board</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The aim of this project is to reevaluate all of the Block specific CSS in TwentyTwenty one and determine if it’s still needed, and if it is, whether to move to Gutenberg; make it configurable via Global Styles, or add it to TT1 Blocks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In many cases this is resulting in new issues and PRs in Gutenberg. We are keeping track of these on the board. Cards that are blocked by a Gutenberg issue should be moved to “Blocked” until the Gutenberg issue is fixed. This will give us a comprehensive list of all the issues we need to fix to get TT1 Blocks launched.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/core/2020/12/11/the-fse-outreach-program-is-officially-starting/\">FSE Outreach Program</a> starting up again soon, we’d like to add TT1 Blocks to the Theme Repository to make it easier for users to test Full Site Editing. We’ll use the name TT1 Blocks to ensure that users don’t get confused with the default theme TwentyTwentyOne.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Requirements for Block Themes</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There was some discussion about the <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/12/14/discussion-requirements-for-full-site-editing-themes/\">requirements for full site editing themes</a>. The following changes were proposed:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Make the theme.json file a requirement</li><li>Remove the requirement for specific php templates (e.g. header.php)</li></ul><p>We need to ensure that the block markup in a theme submission is valid. Exactly how we go about this is something which still needs exploring.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/12/16/block-themes-meeting-notes-for-16-december-2020/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:30:\"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1\";a:1:{s:7:\"post-id\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"19823\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Block-based Themes Meeting Agenda: December 16\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/12/15/block-based-themes-meeting-agenda-december-16/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/12/15/block-based-themes-meeting-agenda-december-16/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 15 Dec 2020 14:22:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Uncategorized\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/?p=19815\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s